text: The Queen's College is one of the colleges of the University of Oxford. It was founded in 1341. The name of the college honors Queen Phillipa of Hanault, the wife of King Edward III. The full name of the college is "The Provost and Scholars of The Queen's College at the University of Oxford". ==References== Category:Colleges of the University of Oxford Category:1340s establishments in England
title: The Queen's College, Oxford
